Modifications made in this derivative work:
  - Ported from Rust to Python (single file, standard library only for the
    default backend).
  - Retargeted from Rust/cargo to embedded C projects that expose a host-side
    CMake + CTest unit suite (Unity). Build and test are run as separate
    cmake/ctest steps, so a non-compiling mutation is reported as BUILD ERROR.
  - Source discovery uses compile_commands.json (the modules actually compiled
    into the tests) instead of globbing src/*.rs.
  - The AWS Bedrock Converse client was replaced by two pluggable backends:
    the local `claude` CLI (claude -p) and the Anthropic API (anthropic SDK).
  - --auto mode inserts new Unity test functions and their RUN_TEST
    registrations (instead of Rust #[test] functions).
